condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :An audited Financial Reports | Description :The Project Implementing Entity, through NELSAP, shall submitunaudited financial reports 45 days after the end of each calendar quarter. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Annual Audits | Description :The Project Implementing Entity, through NELSAP/RCPL, shall submit auditedfinancial statements no later than six months after the close of each fiscal year. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Internal Auditor | Description :The Project Implementing Entity, through NELSAP/RCPL, shall recruit an Internalauditor no later than three months after project effectiveness. | Due Date :30-Mar-2014

Finance Agreement :Power Purchase Escrow Accounts | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall ensure that, except as theAssociation shall otherwise agree, the Power Purchase Agreement will provide that the Utilities (TANESCO, EWSA, REGIDESCO) shallmaintain an amount equal to six months capacity charges in the respective escrow accounts with a depository satisfactory to theProject Implementing Entity. | Due Date :31-Dec-2018

Finance Agreement :Suspension of Deliverly of Energy | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall ensure that, except asthe Association shall otherwise agree, the Power Purchase Agreement will provide that if a Utility fails to make required payments,then delivery of energy to the Utility may be suspended, and such energy can instead be delivered to one of the other ParticipatingCountries. | Due Date :31-Mar-2014
